DataElement.preferredDefinition: A coded value specifying the discreet list of values describing the condition of the specimen at time of receipt at the lab. EXAMPLE(S): Hemolyzed, Icteric, Lipemic

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:The tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object._A state of being, such as a state of health.:A symbol or combination of symbols which is given an arbitrary meaning within a systematized collection of concepts used for data representation.
